-- Christie’s New York Wine Auction Fetches Total of $1.5 Million
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-10-15T18:31:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-15/christie-s-new-york-wine-auction-fetches-total-of-1-5-million.html
Christie’s International’s October
wine auction in  New York  fetched a total $1.5 million, with 96
percent of lots sold by volume and 94 percent by value, the
auction house said in an e-mailed statement.  The top sale was 11 bottles of Chateau Lafite-Rothschild
1982 which went to an Asian trade client for $33,880, including
buyer’s premium. A European trade buyer paid $29,040 for four
bottles of Romanee-Conti Domaine de la Romanee-Conti 1969
Burgundy, Christie’s said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Guy Collins in London at 
 guycollins@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
